Noticed today that if the EventFrame time is the same as the last KeyFrame it will never trigger as the GetEventFrames call checks to see if:

```
eventFrame.time_ >= endTime
```

Which breaks and ignores the event frame if true, shouldn't it be:

```
        if (eventFrame.time_ > endTime)
            break;

        if (eventFrame.time_ >= beginTime)
            eventFrames.Push(&eventFrame);
```

Just want to check I'm not missing some edge case before fixing.

I'm trying to use anisotropic filtering to all textures using this code:

``` c
Renderer* renderer = GetSubsystem<Renderer>();
renderer->SetTextureFilterMode(FILTER_ANISOTROPIC);
renderer->SetTextureAnisotropy(16);
```

But it appears all textures still billinear/trilinear filtered. This issue only happens using OpenGL. It works as it should if I'm using DirectX.

